	^ '<b>Let us build a Morph</b><br>In this first lecture we want to create a <a href="code://Morph">Morph</a> and show it to the user. In order to create a <i>Morph</i> we call "new" on the class - just as we do for every instance of a class in squeak. Then open the <i>Morph</i> in the world we provide to you. This will present your <i>Morph</i> whithin our tutorial world.<br>Do not forget to return your <i>Morph</i> to us, so we can exhibit it in our gallery of first <i>Morph</i>s.' asHtmlText 